description: From Latin exuberatus, past participle of exuberare. See exuberant (“adjective”).

verbs.description: exuberate (third-person singular simple present exuberates, present participle exuberating, simple past and past participle exuberated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To abound; to be in great abundance.
examples: that vast confluence and immensity, that exuberates in God

entries.meaning: (now rare) To develop into (something), by an exuberance of growth.
examples: ‘He might perhaps have become one, if he had had time to ripen, (smiling.) He might have exuberated into an Atheist.’
